Package: neuros-tools
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, python3, python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, gir1.2-appindicator3-0.1, zsh, neovim, git, curl, wmctrl, xclip, xdotool, alsa-utils, espeak-ng
Description: NeurOS AI-powered tools and utilities
 NeurOS is a custom Ubuntu 24.04 LTS-based Linux distribution
 with local LLM integration (Ollama + Mistral 7B) baked in.
 .
 This package contains the core NeurOS command-line tools:
  * nn — Terminal AI assistant with file/context awareness
  * neuros-chat — Local web chat GUI (Flask + HTML/CSS/JS)
  * neuros-model — Model manager (list, pull, switch, benchmark)
  * neuros-git — AI-powered git assistant (commits, reviews, PRs)
  * neuros-agent — System context agent (clipboard, windows, RAG)
  * neuros-snippets — Code snippet manager with AI search
  * neuros-voice — Speech-to-text input
  * neuros-speak — Text-to-speech output
  * neuros-mcp — Model Context Protocol server

Package: neuros-desktop
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, neuros-tools (= ${binary:Version}), gnome-shell, gnome-shell-extensions
Description: NeurOS desktop integration package
 Desktop integration for NeurOS including:
  * System tray applet (neuros-tray)
  * Welcome screen (neuros-welcome)
  * GNOME shell extensions (dash-to-dock, blur-my-shell)
  * Dark theme and custom keyboard shortcuts
  * Wallpaper and visual branding
